src/lib/components/CheckBoxTree.react.js.description:
CheckBoxTree is a component that displays a tree with optional checkboxes.
The tree structure is defined by the `nodes` property. The checked status of the nodes
are stored in the `checked` property.

CheckBoxTree is the Dash encapsulation of the react checkbox tree by Jake Zatecky:
https://github.com/jakezatecky/react-checkbox-tree

id.description:
The ID of this component, used to identify dash components
in callbacks. The ID needs to be unique across all of the
components in an app.

className.name: string
className.description: A classname to add to the node

disabled.name: bool
disabled.description: Whether the node should be disabled

showCheckbox.name: bool
showCheckbox.description: Whether the node should show a checkbox

checked.description: An array of checked node values

expanded.description: An array of expanded node values.

disabled.description: If true, the component will be disabled and nodes cannot be checked

expandDisabled.description: If true, the ability to expand nodes will be disabled

expandOnClick.description:
If true, nodes will be expanded by clicking on labels. Requires
a non-empty onClick function

name.description: Optional name for the hidden <input> element

nameAsArray.description:
If true, the hidden <input> will encode its values as an array
rather than a joined string

nativeCheckboxes.description: If true, native browser checkboxes will be used insted of pseudo-checkbox icons.

noCascade.description: If true, toggling a parent node will not cascade its check state to its children

onlyLeafCheckboxes.description: If true, checkboxes will only be shown for leaf nodes

optimisticToggle.description:
If true, toggling a partially-checked node will select all children.
If false, it will deselect.

showNodeIcon.description: If true, each node will show a parent or leaf icon.

style.description: Defines CSS styles which will override styles previously set.

className.description: Often used with CSS to style elements with common properties.

is_loading.name: bool
is_loading.description: Determines if the component is loading or not

component_name.name: string
component_name.description: Holds the name of the component that is loading

loading_state.description: Object that holds the loading state object coming from dash-renderer

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
